Number one bestselling author and former aide to ex-president Goodluck Jonathan, Pastor Reno Omokri, has urged the Nigerian senate not to confirm the ambassadorial nomination of ex service chiefs as presented by President Muhammadu Buhari. According to him, the ex service chiefs ought to be probed over the death of some innocent Nigerians who died while the service Chiefs were in-charge of their various units.  Reno Omokri, ex-President Goodluck Jonathan's aide has said that it is a lie to say that the Department of State Services, DSS, Director-General, Lawal Daura, who was sacked yesterday by the Acting President Yemi Osinbajo was working for the Senate President Dr Bukola Saraki. August 8, 2018 In "News" Former aide to Ex-President Goodluck Jonathan on electronic media, Pastor Reno Omokri has said that President Muhammadu Buhari does have a certificate scandal against him contrary to claims by the presidency that he does not. March 28, 2017 In "News" Garba Shehu, Senior Special Assistant to the President (Media & Publicity) has asked former aide to ex-President Goodluck Jonathan, Reno Omokri and his acolytes to for forget about presiding over the affairs of Nigeria. May 22, 2018 In "News"